00:42:18,369 --> 00:42:21,330
<i>Just under one minute
remaining in this fourth quarter.</i>

688
00:42:21,413 --> 00:42:24,083
<i>Suns lead 98 to 94.</i>

689
00:42:25,376 --> 00:42:29,547
<i>Frank Johnson, not the man that the Suns
would've wanted to take that shot.</i>

690
00:42:30,214 --> 00:42:32,383
<i>And Jordan was able to go the distance.</i>

691
00:42:32,466 --> 00:42:34,009
<i>Worst thing to happen!</i>

692
00:42:34,093 --> 00:42:36,679
<i>Let 'em score and use up
very few precious seconds!</i>

693
00:42:36,762 --> 00:42:38,657
<i>It's Chicago's game
to win or lose.</i>

694
00:42:38,681 --> 00:42:41,767
<i>They put 14.1 seconds up,
Suns lead by two.</i>

695
00:42:41,850 --> 00:42:44,728
<i>They're gonna put the ball
in Michael Jordan's hands.</i>

696
00:42:44,812 --> 00:42:48,774
<i>It's come down to
this possession. The Suns by two.</i>

697
00:42:49,358 --> 00:42:50,693
<i>And Pippen got the snatch.</i>

698
00:42:51,235 --> 00:42:52,861
<i>Here's Paxson. For three!</i>

699
00:42:53,362 --> 00:42:57,324
<i>Yes! The Bulls
take a one-point lead and...</i>

700
00:42:58,325 --> 00:43:02,204
<i>Yeah! Hits the three!
The crowd is stunned.</i>

701
00:43:02,288 --> 00:43:04,582
<i>John Paxson
nails the three!</i>

702
00:43:04,665 --> 00:43:08,460
<i>That's the first score by anybody
other than Michael Jordan</i>

703
00:43:08,544 --> 00:43:10,379
<i>in the entire fourth quarter!</i>

704
00:43:10,462 --> 00:43:12,673
The ball was not supposed to come to me.

705
00:43:13,465 --> 00:43:15,342
But as a player, you're always ready.

706
00:43:17,344 --> 00:43:21,473
And for me, personally,
it was pretty special.

707
00:43:23,017 --> 00:43:24,226
<i>It's all over!</i>

708
00:43:24,310 --> 00:43:30,024
<i>The Chicago Bulls have made it
three straight NBA championships.</i>

709
00:43:30,107 --> 00:43:33,694
<i>A three-point shot by John Paxson,
the game winner.</i>

710
00:43:33,777 --> 00:43:36,614
I have no problem losing to Michael.

711
00:43:36,697 --> 00:43:39,742
Losing to Michael,
there's no shame in that.

712
00:43:41,702 --> 00:43:43,829
Sports are like a gunfight.

713
00:43:45,497 --> 00:43:48,626
And... we lost to the fastest gun.

714
00:43:50,753 --> 00:43:51,753
Whoo!

715
00:43:55,633 --> 00:43:57,926
<i>Physically,
I was getting exhausted,</i>

716
00:43:59,178 --> 00:44:02,848
<i>but, mentally, I was
way past exhausted.</i>

717
00:44:04,433 --> 00:44:06,268
<i>When you try to do something repetitively,</i>

718
00:44:06,352 --> 00:44:10,397
<i>you lose some of the hunger
and some of the edge.</i>

719
00:44:19,323 --> 00:44:22,451
Here's the thing. I think,
when we won the third championship,

720
00:44:23,202 --> 00:44:28,499
being around him,
there was more relief than true joy.

721
00:44:28,582 --> 00:44:32,503
Like, it's over, you know? He was tired.

722
00:44:34,088 --> 00:44:36,965
The aftermath, you kind of feel like...

723
00:44:41,220 --> 00:44:42,554
"What are we gonna do?"

724
00:44:44,139 --> 00:44:48,352
<i>This has been a very hard and trying time.
This has been a tough year.</i>

725
00:44:50,729 --> 00:44:52,398
Do I have to do anything else?

726
00:44:52,481 --> 00:44:54,692
- Can I just sit here for a few minutes?
- Yup.

727
00:44:54,775 --> 00:44:56,026
Did you want to call your wife?

728
00:44:56,110 --> 00:44:57,695
Yeah, man. Yes.

729
00:45:05,786 --> 00:45:08,789
Is it... Is it joy or is it relief
or is it a combination?

730
00:45:08,872 --> 00:45:10,833
This has been a great year,
but a tough year.

731
00:45:10,916 --> 00:45:14,002
It's both. It's a relief.
Plus it's great to win.

732
00:45:14,086 --> 00:45:15,587
I think we've gone through a lot.

733
00:45:15,671 --> 00:45:18,507
Me, personally, I've gone through a lot
up to now, but...

734
00:45:18,590 --> 00:45:21,468
To cap it off this way
means a lot to me, believe me.

735
00:45:32,146 --> 00:45:33,564
My fame is...

736
00:45:34,314 --> 00:45:36,066
It was good at the beginning.

737
00:45:36,150 --> 00:45:38,610
Any time people talk about you
in a positive way,

738
00:45:38,694 --> 00:45:44,408
yeah, it's great to hear those comments,
but now that you are... on a pedestal,

739
00:45:44,491 --> 00:45:46,452
it's not just the positive talking
that you hear.

740
00:45:46,535 --> 00:45:49,538
You hear some points and some people
taking shots at you, and...

741
00:45:50,164 --> 00:45:55,919
that really changes the whole idea
of being out there for people to see you.

742
00:45:56,003 --> 00:45:58,964
You wanna get behind closed doors
so people don't know you as much.

743
00:45:59,047 --> 00:46:01,967
So, I'm at that stage in my career
and my life that...

744
00:46:02,634 --> 00:46:06,221
I'd rather get behind closed doors
than to be out there in the spotlight

745
00:46:06,305 --> 00:46:10,058
to be taking shots from everyone
that really don't know you as a person.

746
00:46:13,312 --> 00:46:15,147
<i>If I had the chance
to do it all over again,</i>

747
00:46:15,647 --> 00:46:18,275
<i>I would never wanna be considered
a role model.</i>

748
00:46:19,568 --> 00:46:21,987
<i>It's like a game
that's stacked against me.</i>

749
00:46:22,070 --> 00:46:23,655
<i>There's no way I can win.</i>

750
00:46:57,272 --> 00:47:00,275
I think I've been asked
about a million times,

751
00:47:00,359 --> 00:47:02,778
"Is he gonna quit, is he not gonna quit?"

752
00:47:02,861 --> 00:47:04,738
I'm having fun making up stuff.

753
00:47:06,490 --> 00:47:12,120
No one wants me to walk out,
knowing that I can still play the game.

754
00:47:12,204 --> 00:47:14,915
- But I wanna leave two years before...
- Right.

755
00:47:14,998 --> 00:47:17,835
...my skills say
that I can't play this game.

756
00:47:17,918 --> 00:47:18,918
Mm-hmm.

757
00:47:19,628 --> 00:47:22,881
I don't wanna miss my time to go.
There's a lot of players...

758
00:47:23,757 --> 00:47:26,093
say that, "I'm gonna play
until I can't play ever again."

759
00:47:26,176 --> 00:47:28,720
- Right.
- I think Patrick said that one time.

760
00:47:28,804 --> 00:47:32,474
That they'll have to carry him
off the court. You know.

761
00:47:32,558 --> 00:47:34,810
- Mm-hmm.
- That's a... Ain't never...

762
00:47:34,893 --> 00:47:37,563
Nobody gonna carry me off the court.
I wanna walk off the court.

763
00:47:40,357 --> 00:47:43,360
A lot of people say,
"Well, you're gonna miss it."

764
00:47:44,236 --> 00:47:47,114
I'm not... I'm not sure
if I'm gonna miss it.

765
00:47:49,241 --> 00:47:50,659
I don't think I'm gonna miss it.

766
00:47:51,326 --> 00:47:53,912
<i>...Michael is Zen-calm
around the Bulls,</i>

767
00:47:53,996 --> 00:47:55,956
<i>as they start their postseason tonight.</i>

768
00:47:56,039 --> 00:47:59,126
<i>A calm that blocks out the speculation
about Jordan's retirement,</i>

769
00:47:59,209 --> 00:48:02,004
<i>Phil Jackson's departure,
all the front-office politics.</i>

770
00:48:02,087 --> 00:48:04,464
<i>If indeed this is the fabled last dance,</i>

771
00:48:04,548 --> 00:48:06,800
<i>then pay attention
because it does begin tonight</i>

772
00:48:06,884 --> 00:48:08,927
<i>for a team
that has a rested Scottie Pippen,</i>

773
00:48:09,011 --> 00:48:11,430
<i>the best player in the world,
the top eastern seed,</i>

774
00:48:11,513 --> 00:48:14,308
<i>and five games to
tune it up against the New Jersey Nets.</i>

